   "source": [
    "Note that, the model is instructed to return its response in JSON format.\n",
    "1. JSON is a lightweight, structured format(key-value pairs)that maks it easy to parse the LLM's output programmatically.\n",
    "2. Here, we require two fields:\n",
    "   - feedback: a short critque of the current chart\n",
    "   - refined_code: an improved Python code snippet wrapped in <execute_python> tags.\n",
    "we also include \"constraints\" section in the prompt. These rules(eg: use matplotlib only, save the file to a specific path, call plt.close() at the end) help the model generate consistent, runnable code that fits the workflow. Without these constraints, the output might vary too much or include unwanted formatting."
   ]
